I'd prefer the criteria version of this:
return (List<Encounter>) sessionFactory.getCurrentSession().createCriteria(Encounter.class).createAlias("patient", "p")
				.createAlias("p.identifiers", "pi")
				.add(eq("pi.identifier", patientIdentifier))
				.list();

My reason for favouring Criteria over HQL or JPQL is that it will make things easier when we get to implementing search across multiple properties.

